PREAMBLE
────────

V-CoPanel is a portable, zero-dependency local development environment for
Windows, engineered in pure Go by the VJECTS Architecture Team.

This software is a fully self-funded, independent project. It was conceived,
designed, architected, and shipped with zero external funding, zero corporate
sponsorship, and zero third-party financial backing — entirely by its creator
out of personal necessity and a deep frustration with the existing tools on
the Windows platform.

This license is designed to protect that independent creative effort, keep the
core engine free and accessible to the community, preserve the integrity of
the VJECTS brand, and establish a fair and transparent framework for any
third-party developers who build substantial, meaningful additions on top of
this foundation.


SECTION 1 — DEFINITIONS
────────────────────────

"Software"          Refers to V-CoPanel and all its source code, compiled
                    binaries, assets, documentation, and associated files
                    as distributed in this repository.

"Copyright Holder"  Refers exclusively to VJECTS (vjects.com), the sole
                    creator and maintainer of the Software.

"You" / "User"      Any individual or legal entity exercising permissions
                    granted by this license.

"Derivative Work"   Any modification, fork, or redistribution of the
                    Software, whether partial or complete.

"Commercial Use"    The sale, sublicensing, or fee-based distribution of
                    the Software or any Derivative Work.

"Official Domain"   vjects.com, the sole and exclusive authoritative web
                    presence of VJECTS and this Software.


