SECTION 4 — FAIR COMMERCIALIZATION & THIRD-PARTY MONETIZATION
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

The Copyright Holder believes in rewarding genuine, high-value contribution.
Commercial sale or fee-based distribution of the Software or Derivative Works
is PROHIBITED, except under the following strict conditions — all of which
must be satisfied simultaneously:

  a) SUBSTANTIVE ORIGINAL CONTRIBUTION
     The Derivative Work must introduce at least one (1) major, independent,
     and substantive new feature or service that is not present in any
     official upstream release of V-CoPanel. The following categories
     explicitly DO NOT qualify as substantive contributions:
       – Minor bug fixes or dependency updates
       – Visual reskinning, theme changes, or icon replacements
       – Configuration file adjustments or parameter tuning
       – Language translations or documentation additions
       – Repackaging without functional additions

  b) MANDATORY NAMING FORMAT
     Any commercialized Derivative Work must retain "V-CoPanel" as its
     base name and must follow this exact format:

         V-CoPanel — [Developer or Company Name] Edition

     Example: "V-CoPanel — Acme Edition"

     It may not be sold under any other name that omits "V-CoPanel".

  c) CREDIT & OPEN CORE REQUIREMENT
     The commercial seller must:
       – Prominently credit VJECTS (vjects.com) as the original author.
       – Ensure that all features inherited from the official V-CoPanel
         release remain free, accessible, and open-source within that
         edition. Only the seller's own added value may be monetized.


